WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.709 --> 00:00:02.961
The act of design,

00:00:02.961 --> 00:00:04.629
trying to convey a feeling,

00:00:05.296 --> 00:00:06.923
only humans can do that.

00:00:07.799 --> 00:00:09.551
Claude is a great partner

00:00:09.551 --> 00:00:10.719
to power Figma Make

00:00:10.719 --> 00:00:13.555
because every single 
person who has taste

00:00:13.555 --> 00:00:16.016
can just enact it all that easier.

00:00:16.766 --> 00:00:17.809
We’ve spent a ton of time

00:00:17.809 --> 00:00:18.643
at Figma figuring out how to

00:00:18.643 --> 00:00:19.519
effectively translate

00:00:19.519 --> 00:00:20.770
what you have on a canvas

00:00:20.770 --> 00:00:22.147
to pixel perfect code

00:00:22.147 --> 00:00:23.732
that you can just start from.

00:00:24.315 --> 00:00:26.443
The more that we've worked
with Claude in particular,

00:00:26.443 --> 00:00:28.153
clearly it just seems 
to know code

00:00:28.153 --> 00:00:29.362
better than most of the models

00:00:29.362 --> 00:00:30.697
and produces code that 
we think developers

00:00:30.697 --> 00:00:31.948
would actually want to write.

00:00:31.948 --> 00:00:34.951
Claude is such a evidently
good coding model.

00:00:35.243 --> 00:00:36.202
I don't code.

00:00:36.828 --> 00:00:38.496
One of the best innovations

00:00:38.496 --> 00:00:40.040
of the past couple of years

00:00:40.040 --> 00:00:41.541
is that I really don't have to

00:00:41.541 --> 00:00:43.084
in order to create the 
things I want to do.

00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:45.670
You'll be able to do things
now with Claude

00:00:45.670 --> 00:00:47.130
that would have otherwise

00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:49.466
taken you a lot of time,
a lot of energy.

00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:51.509
And I'm really, really excited, actually,

00:00:51.509 --> 00:00:53.386
to see all of the new ideas

00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:56.222
that people are able to produce
with Figma Make.

00:00:56.222 --> 00:00:58.058
Design is going to be

00:00:58.058 --> 00:01:01.186
a much more accessible 
practice for people.

00:01:01.186 --> 00:01:02.312
I think I'm most excited about 

00:01:02.312 --> 00:01:03.938
any tools that we can 
create to help folks

00:01:03.938 --> 00:01:06.024
get to the end products
not just faster,

00:01:06.024 --> 00:01:07.108
but with higher quality,

00:01:07.108 --> 00:01:09.235
get more ideas out, 
do more explorations,

00:01:09.611 --> 00:01:10.779
and end up at the results

00:01:10.779 --> 00:01:11.905
that they want to end up with.

